                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.79614/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-02-03T12:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1927—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 7:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Referring to the Department’s telegram of February 1, 5 p.m. Parada went to
                    San Salvador 10 days ago. It is thought here that he is backed by the Mexican
                    Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geissler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
